 Leiden University. </a></b> </p>
<p>
<center> <img src="Me.jpeg" width="350"> </center>
</p>
<p> Before this, I obtained my bachelors's degree <i> Dutch Language and Culture,</i> during which I specialized in modern literature.
I was born in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norg"> Norg</a>, a small village in the north of The Netherlands. After finishing secondary school in Assen, I moved to Leiden, where I went on to study Political Science.
After finishing my propaedeutic year, I decided to go down a different path and started the Dutch Language and Culture degree.
During the third year, I enrolled into the minor programme <i> Boek, Boekhandel en Uitgeverij </i> in preperation to my current master's degree.
I finally finished my degree with a thesis on peritextual elements and the way they frame our perception of literary works. </p>
